13/09/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Croatian Consul to Montenegro, Petar Poljanic, praised conditions for ethnic Croats there on Sunday (12 September), saying the situation is better than 50 or even 100 years ago. Noting there are an estimated 15,000 Croats living in Montenegro, Poljanic said that for the first time since WWII, the Croat minority is organised and has its own party, the Croatian Civil Initiative. 
In other news, Croatiaâ€™s EU bid received support Friday from Cyprus. During a meeting in Zagreb with Croatian counterpart Miomir Zuzul, Cypriot Foreign Minister George Iacovou offered to share experiences concerning the accession process. (HINA, HRT - 12/09/04; AFP - 11/09/04) 
